h the estimation of the Bayesian\nevidence. Finally, we demonstrate that our approach is robust to real noise as\nmeasured in field data. This work lays the foundations for efficient, accurate\nfuture joint determinations of event location and moment tensor, and associated\nuncertainties, which are ultimately key for accurately characterising\nhuman-induced and natural earthquakes, and for enhanced quantitative seismic\nhazard assessments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jan 2021 19:51:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 28 Oct 2022 13:43:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-31"}
