the inferred\ndistances, the energy released in both flares is on par with that of the\nDecember 27, 2004 superflare from the Galactic magnetar SGR 1806-20, but with a\nhigher peak luminosity. Taken all together, this makes GRB 200415A and its twin\nGRB 051103 the most significant candidates for extragalactic magnetar giant\nflares, both a factor of five more luminous than the brightest Galactic\nmagnetar flare observed previously, thus providing an important step towards a\nbetter understanding of this fascinating phenomenon.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jan 2021 14:39:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-14"}
